com.gisfederal.gpudb.protocol

Class VisualizeImageRequest

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.gisfederal.gpudb.protocol.VisualizeImageRequest
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    org.apache.avro.generic.GenericContainer, org.apache.avro.generic.IndexedRecord

    public class VisualizeImageRequest
extends Object
implements org.apache.avro.generic.IndexedRecord
    A set of parameters for GPUdb.visualizeImage(VisualizeImageRequest).

    Generates 'class break' rasterized image tiles for an area of interest using the given tables and the provided parameters.

    All color values must be in the format RRGGBB or AARRGGBB (to specify the alpha value).

      • VisualizeImageRequest

        public VisualizeImageRequest(List<String> tableNames,
                     List<String> worldTableNames,
                     String xColumnName,
                     String yColumnName,
                     List<List<String>> trackIds,
                     double minX,
                     double maxX,
                     double minY,
                     double maxY,
                     int width,
                     int height,
                     String projection,
                     long bgColor,
                     List<Boolean> doPoints,
                     List<Boolean> doShapes,
                     List<Boolean> doTracks,
                     List<Boolean> doSymbology,
                     List<Long> pointcolors,
                     List<Integer> pointsizes,
                     List<String> pointshapes,
                     List<Integer> shapelinewidths,
                     List<Long> shapelinecolors,
                     List<Long> shapefillcolors,
                     List<Integer> tracklinewidths,
                     List<Long> tracklinecolors,
                     List<Integer> trackmarkersizes,
                     List<Long> trackmarkercolors,
                     List<String> trackmarkershapes,
                     List<Long> trackheadcolors,
                     List<Integer> trackheadsizes,
                     List<String> trackheadshapes,
                     Map<String,String> options)
        Constructs a VisualizeImageRequest object with the specified parameters.
        Parameters:
        tableNames - Name of the table containing the data for the various layers to be rendered.
        worldTableNames - Optional name of the tables containing the data for the entire track when the tableNames contains only part of the track data, but the entire track has to be rendered.
        xColumnName - Name of the column containing the x coordinates.
        yColumnName - Name of the column containing the y coordinates.
        trackIds - Tracks from the tableNames to be rendered.
        minX - Lower bound for the x values.
        maxX - Upper bound for the x values.
        minY - Lower bound for the y values.
        maxY - Upper bound for the y values.
        width - Width of the generated image.
        height - Height of the generated image.
        projection - Spatial Reference System (i.e. EPSG Code).
        bgColor - Background color of the generated image
        doPoints - Rasterize point data toggle.
        doShapes - Rasterize shapes toggle.
        doTracks - Rasterize tracks toggle.
        doSymbology - Rasterize symbols toggle.
        pointcolors - RGB color value in hex for the points.
        pointsizes - Size of points. The minimum allowed value is 0. The maximum allowed value is 20.
        pointshapes - Shape of the point.
        shapelinewidths - Width of the lines. The minimum allowed value is 0. The maximum allowed value is 20.
        shapelinecolors - RGB color values in hex for the line.
        shapefillcolors - RGB color values in hex for the fill color of the shapes. Use '-1' for no fill.
        tracklinewidths - Width of the track lines. '0' implies do not draw track lines. The minimum allowed value is 0. The maximum allowed value is 20.
        tracklinecolors - RGB color values for the track lines.
        trackmarkersizes - Size of the track point markers. The minimum allowed value is 0. The maximum allowed value is 20.
        trackmarkercolors - Color of the track point markers.
        trackmarkershapes - Shape of track point markers.
        trackheadcolors - Color of track head markers.
        trackheadsizes - Size of track head markers. The minimum allowed value is 0. The maximum allowed value is 20.
        trackheadshapes - Shape of track head markers.
        options - Optional parameters.
